00:24:21.510 --> 00:24:24.370
they're meant to come to England to document
that native rituals of

00:24:24.370 --> 00:24:31.460
the tribal people called the English. So they're
on the other side of the island and we're

00:24:31.460 --> 00:24:35.159
on Tanna and I'd heard about this film so
I was really intrigued

00:24:35.159 --> 00:24:40.029
by thinking about the idea of again a contemporary
art center in the middle of all this swirling,

00:24:40.029 --> 00:24:45.220
strange, kind of very interesting bubbling
of not only

00:24:45.220 --> 00:24:49.020
"The Island" is the embodiment of one of my
favorite science fiction writers phrases.

00:24:49.020 --> 00:24:51.940
William Gibson has a great phrase where he
