00:24:51.940 --> 00:24:56.470
here. It's just unevenly distributed." And
you can see these guys dressed in traditional

00:24:56.470 --> 00:24:59.520
gear in the middle of these skyscrapers in,
you know, downtown

00:24:59.520 --> 00:25:04.020
London and that is the embodiment of this
kind of collage aesthetic. You have all of

00:25:04.020 --> 00:25:07.030
these different versions of how people have
the ideological frameworks of

00:25:07.030 --> 00:25:11.419
how they organize information and you have
this social network that value and embody

00:25:11.419 --> 00:25:14.649
these kinds of values but above all you have
different forms of

00:25:14.649 --> 00:25:19.940
technology, social technologies that people
use to construct their sense of aesthetics.

00:25:19.940 --> 00:25:24.150
So as an artist, writer, and musician I deejay
all over the world and

00:25:24.150 --> 00:25:28.419
I've deejayed in places as remote as Antarctica
and I've just got back from the North Pole

00:25:28.419 --> 00:25:32.130
